  "text": "Candida albicans commonly colonizes the urethra. It can be found in the semen and may affect in vitro fertilization. C. albicans has an inhibitory effect on human sperm motility and impairs the ultrastructure of human spermatozoa, which could be associated with male infertility [CITATION_1] .",
